                  market, esg, bi, governance, etl, audit, staging)
  Tables:     30+ across all schemas
  Views:      25+ analytical views
  Procedures: 12+ stored procedures
  Functions:   3 inline table-valued functions
  Triggers:    1 audit trigger
  Indexes:     6 composite covering indexes
 
SQL Skills Demonstrated:
  Window Functions  : RANK, DENSE_RANK, ROW_NUMBER, NTILE,
                      PERCENT_RANK, CUME_DIST, LAG, LEAD,
                      FIRST_VALUE, LAST_VALUE, SUM OVER,
                      AVG OVER, STDEV OVER, ROWS/RANGE frames
  Joins             : INNER, LEFT, CROSS, CROSS APPLY, Self-join
  CTEs              : Simple, Chained (4-level), Recursive
  Dynamic SQL       : sp_executesql, PIVOT generation
  Computed Columns  : AS (expression) – stored and virtual
  Stored Procedures : SCD2, Amortisation, Stress Test, Pivot
  Functions         : Inline TVF, Scalar via procedures
  Triggers          : AFTER INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE audit logging
  Indexes           : Composite, covering, on FK columns
  Data Modelling    : Star Schema, SCD Type 2, Fact/Dim tables
  Financial Math    : ROIC, NOPAT, PD/LGD/EAD, Amortisation PMT
  Credit Risk       : Basel III EL, IFRS 9 staging, PD scale
  Fraud Detection   : Benford Law proxy, duplicate analysis, scoring
  ESG Analytics     : E/S/G scoring, carbon intensity, sector rank
 
